<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">648T.006/12: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-06T16:00:00-05:00">January 6, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>38. Department’s mail instruction 1134 December 26<note n="60" xml:id="d101fn60">Not printed.</note> with regard to Kenya
                                Colony regulations effective November 15, 1939, and American
                                commercial rights in that colony.</p>
                            <p>The Japanese Embassy has made inquiry of us concerning this subject
                                and we are informing the Japanese Embassy that you have been
                                instructed to bring the matter appropriately to the attention of the
                                British Government. When you make the approach to British officials
                                contemplated in the final paragraph of the Department’s instruction
                                of December 26 the Department suggests that you inform those
                                officials orally of the Japanese approach to us and of our
                                reply.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>